#Text=Yeah , and they ’re theists .
#Text=They believe that Set exists and that their priests can commune with him and that their founder is the voice of Set .
#Text=So , it ’s like , good that they left for housecleaning .

#Text=But Zeena went and joined them and became High Priestess because Michael Aquino has this Anton LaVey obsession , which is obvious since he wrote a book about him that 's about a thousand pages , so he made her the High Priestess of their organization .
#Text=Then she left to form an even more orthodox Setian group called “ The Storm ” , which to us is just funny .
#Text=Such theatrics .
#Text=His oldest daughter Karla is n't a very bright girl .
#Text=She kind of hung around the background and once in a while she would come out to speak in public and support her father .
#Text=When Xerxes was born she kind of got miffed because she was n't the center of attention .
#Text=Karla is also jealous type .
#Text=She withdrew from her father , which hurt him a lot .
#Text=How did the legal wrangling surrounding his estate pan out ?
#Text=They finally settled .
#Text=What ended up happening is he had written a will .
#Text=Anton LaVey 's idea was that if he acknowledged he is going to die , then he 'd be giving in to death , so he did n't want to go to an attorney and make out a will .
#Text=He was very feisty and had his own perspective on that .
#Text=So he finally wrote a will out and signed it , but it was n't notarized and there were no witnesses .
#Text=So when it came to court they said it was n't good enough .
#Text=They basically split everything up between the three children , so Karla and Zeena and Xerxes all got part of the estate .
#Text=Who received the copyright to The Satanic Bible ?
#Text=The estate .
#Text=The money that comes in from that gets split up and goes to the three kids .
#Text=Also there is a small percentage that goes to LaVey 's companion , Diane Hegarty ; she says LaVey .
#Text=But they were never married and had a falling out in the early 1980 's .
#Text=She went off and left Satanism and sued him for palimony and he had to sell his house because of all of that , and he sold it to an old friend and member .
#Text=Diane got a pile of money and she got a tiny percentage of the books that had been written up to that point .

#Text=Every once in a while she comes creeping in off the periphery to say , “ Ah ! I 'm Diane LaVey ! ” and it 's like , you were Diane Hegarty and you were kind of involved in it , but before the Satanic Panic happened you left and had nothing to do with it .
#Text=She was never someone who wrote or said anything of interest .
#Text=She was just the pretty blonde wife of Anton LaVey .
#Text=She was a nice figurehead , but was n't of much use beyond that .
